Description: Egypt, street-scene in Alexandria. Row of three-storey buildings with shops at left, motor-car and horse-drawn carriage driving along street. Small group of adult males standing and walking in foreground, wearing gowns and head-gear. European adult males walking at right and riding in carriage. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
